Durban - A drug dealer has begun serving his 15-year-jail sentence after being found guilty of dealing in drugs in the Pongola Regional Court in KwaZulu-Natal on Monday. The court sentenced Maliki Erick Ngobeni, 45, to 15 years imprisonment for dealing in drugs. Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo a spokesperson for the Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation (DPCI) aka Hawks said the Richards Bay Serious Organised Crime unit received information about a vehicle that was traveling from Golela Port of Entry towards Pongola The local police were alerted and the said vehicle was intercepted on the N2, near Sitilo on May 4,2017. "Police searched the vehicle and found 145 bags of heroin powder to the street value of approximately R101 million. Ngobeni and his two passengers were immediately placed under arrest.  Hawks’ investigation revealed that the drugs were coming from Mozambique destined to Johannesburg. It was also discovered that Ngobeni was the mastermind behind the drug trafficking,"Mhlongo explained. Ngobeni's bail was successfully opposed and he appeared in court several times before he was convicted and sentenced. Daily News 